article.headline: LIU Brooklyn 86, Mount St. Mary's 72
article.story: BROOKLYN, N.Y. -- E.J. Reed came off the bench and scored career-high 21 points and grabbed seven rebounds as LIU Brooklyn beat Mount St. Mary's 86-72 Saturday in a Northeast Conference matchup. C.J. Garner added 14 points and seven rebounds, and Jamal Olasewere finished with a double-double, 16 points and a game-high 11 boards to help the LIU (6-20, 1-3) outrebound Mount St. Mary's 40-27. Trailing 54-37 at the 16:22 mark, Mount St. Mary's (6-9, 1-3) went on a 17-6 run make it 60-54 with 9:45 left to play. That was the closest the Mountaineers would get as LIU Brooklyn closed the game on a 26-18 run. LIU shot 58.5 percent (31 for 53) for the game and outscored Mount St. Mary's 44-20 in the paint. Rashad Whack led the Mountaineers with 18 points, and Raven Barber added 10 points off the bench. Both players recorded six rebounds.
